Who are we?We are Court & Country, an a cappella vocal ensemble from the greater Chicago area. Our main repertoire is medieval and renaissance choral music. Our group’s name indicates our desire to showcase early music from all stations and styles, from the courts of nobility, to chapels and churches, to public taverns.  Our mission is to bring early music to popular audiences who don’t normally hear it. We’ve also adapted a handful of modern pieces to serve our more eclectic audiences. We offer education in our entertainment, include humor in our presentation, and focus on research to support everything we do. Why do we need your help?We’ve celebrated our 10th anniversary in 2019. In celebration of this milestone, we recorded songs for our second album, titled “Both Kinds of Musick.” We are working very hard to make our second album even better than our first album (“Journey Through Time”). To do everything to the level we hope for requires more funds than we currently have. In addition, we could not have celebrated more than 10 years as a performing group without the support of our fans and friends—so we want to make you an important part of this celebration too. The songs are already recorded, so the primary work for the album is already complete.  But we need your help for the production costs. With your assistance, we can resolve copyrights for sheet music and lyrics, reward our dear friends who worked for free or low cost, enhance the recordings, commission professional artwork, expand the liner notes, etc. What you can get:Our reward options include:
Public acknowledgements of your gift;
Electronic and physical copies of the album--including signed copies;
Bundles of this album with our first album; and
Various Court & Country logo items.
 How much we seek: $2,500 Where the money goes:
Payment for the sound engineer;
Donations for the venues where we recorded the music;
Mastering the audio files;
Licensing costs for any published sheet music;
CD production costs;
Purchasing the crowdfunding perks;
Payment for the videographer;
Custom cover art;
Enhanced liner notes; and
Live recording of the 10th anniversary concert.
 What we’ve done so far:
Held numerous planning meetings;
Selected repertoire for the CD;
Held three recording sessions;
Recorded and mixed 77 different files of 24 possible album tracks;
Listened to and evaluated all 77 files;
Selected mastering services;
Drafted cover art;
Wrote, recorded and edited the promotional video; and
Ordered samples of rewards for evaluation.
 Timeline:Our goal is to have everything for the album ready for production by the end of the year so that the CDs can be manufactured in early 2020 with delivery in February-March 2020. Electronic files will be available a little earlier when the album is mastered and ready for manufacture. Risks and Challenges:The music is already recorded. We are working on preparing it for mastering. The main risk is unforeseen delays in remixing a couple of the tracks, mastering all the tracks and manufacturing the album, but the timeline should accommodate moderate delays. There may also be delays in delivery of the rewards, but we believe we've chosen a vendor who is reliable vendor both for quality and delivery times, to mitigate that risk. We will keep everyone informed should anything come up to affect the album or the rewards. More information About Us:If you would like to know more about us, see the following social media and contact sites:            Website: http://courtandcountry.com            Email: courtandcountry@gmail.com            Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/CourtAndCountry            Twitter: @courtandcountry            Instagram: @courtandcountry Live Performances if You Like What You See:If you are a new friend, we hope you like what you hear and also seek us out in our 2019 live performances, such as: 
WindyCon Convention on Sunday, November 16  at noon at the Westin in Lombard, IL;
RavenStone Castle in Harvard, IL on Saturday, December 14 at 2:00 pm; or
10th Anniversary Concert on Friday, December 20 at Grace Lutheran Church in River Forest, IL.
See our website or Facebook page for more information on all three concerts or contact us via email or social media. 2020 performances are in the planning stages.Thank YouWe are truly grateful for anything you can contribute, no matter the amount. We value the support of our friends and fans very highly and could not have succeeded in our musical journey without you.
